I've made this recipe twice now and used boneless center cut pork chops pounded out real thin. The second time I made it I dredged the pork chops in flour and added a tablespoon of butter in the sauce at the end. The flour and butter help make the sauce a little thicker and richer. Very easy and quick to make.

