I felt like I was cheating, when I made this recipe, because it was so easy and fast to put together, and the meal definitely tasted like it would have been more time consuming to make. When I don't have any fresh rosemary around, I use 1t. dry. I like to double the sauce, and the sundried tomatoes, as I like to serve the whole thing over pasta or orzo. Thicken the sauce abit with 1t. of arrowroot,(or cornstarch could be used instead, but love the silky results with arrowroot),mixed with a little water. Bon apetit!

